<p style="font-size:1.15em;color:#444">Florida has roughly nine accredited nurse anesthesia programs spread from Miami to Jacksonville to Fort Myers, giving in-state ICU nurses real choice. Here's how the programs compare and how to put together a competitive Florida application.</p>

<div class="hero-note">
<strong>Florida CRNA market context:</strong> Florida's aging population, heavy surgical volume, and large hospital systems make it a durable CRNA job market. Programs are competitive — most cohorts admit only 24–60 students — but the state's nine-program density means Florida nurses can usually train without leaving the state. New graduate salaries commonly land in the $185,000–$215,000 range.
</div>

<h2>Accredited CRNA Programs in Florida (2026)</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Program</th><th>Degree</th><th>Length</th><th>Location</th></tr>
